cs.NI, cs.AI, cs.SY, cs.IT, cs.MM 

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper proposes a resource allocation scheme for V2V communication. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper proposes a matching game algorithm to solve the resource allocation problem. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is another possible category as the paper deals with optimizing the performance of a V2V communication system. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is a possible category as the paper deals with optimizing the tradeoffs between load and successful transmissions. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is a less likely category as the paper does not explicitly deal with multimedia data, but it does deal with optimizing the signal-to-interference-plus-noise ratio (SINR) which is relevant to multimedia applications.
